@douglasbagnall, the cause isn't in '\n' at the end, rather in line 65 in https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/blob/622995a50130824da120e81f31a048ac38966d06/src/_pytest/assertion/truncate.py#L63-L70
So in your particular case if it's written "2 lines hidden" it really does mean "1 line hidden + last line was [maybe] truncated" - and in Your case last line isn't really truncated :thinking:. I'm not sure why it's done that way, maybe @RonnyPfannschmidt  can share a thought?
I'm going to do something similar to what You'd suggested, though.
